  "description": "A journal entry line is an individual debit or credit line within a journal entry that specifies a single account, amount, and (optionally) financial dimensions.\r\n\r\nA journal entry is made up of one or more lines, and the total of all debit lines must equal the total of all credit lines.\r\n\r\nAn item line of journal entry representing the movement of money of a certain aspect which is accounted for a specific account.",
